[ ] finish routing CLI writes through the durability primitive ~$ write-durability closed with core's write sites converted, but the CLI's own save paths still call naive std::fs::write — every complete, update, cancel, and delete goes through commands/mod.rs save_file, so a crash mid-write can truncate a source-of-truth file. the crash-safety layer exists and is tested; the most common writes bypass it $!1+cli #019f268f-eb32-747c-aa98-37eabca59a11
    >[ ] sweep the remaining naive workspace-data writes $ plan.rs writes .ics with fs::write, charter.rs writes charter markdown in three places, archive.rs writes the completed file directly — route each through durability::atomic_write. exempt: write_or_print user-directed output, init.rs one-time bootstrap, gen_man. SEQUENCED after the caldav reconcile shell because its step 1 lifts the plan.rs mirror-path logic into core — sweeping plan.rs first would collide with that move $+cli  <019f12d4-4f7c-7bc2-9c76-b048067d43e8#019f268f-eb35-7c28-9704-bfb7efbd714d
    >[ ] add a guard so the seam cannot silently reopen $ deny std::fs::write under src/commands via clippy disallowed-methods or a small test that greps the tree; this is the process lesson from write-durability made mechanical $+cli #019f268f-eb36-71c5-be00-a0ff2b54292b
[ ] unify action reference resolution on the core resolver ~$ three implementations exist — core reference::resolve_reference is the real one, mutations::resolve_reference is a flat-list copy, and act_matches in commands/action.rs is a boolean check used by all mutating commands. act_matches breaks the spec's resolution order, an earlier name-contains match shadows a later exact alias, so complete can close the wrong action $!1+cli,bug #019f268f-eb37-7ef1-acb7-dc303a66d7ae
    >[ ] fix alias-beats-name precedence in mutating commands $ this is the user-facing bug and lands first — find_act_mut must prefer full uuid, then short uuid, then alias, then name-contains across the whole list rather than first-match-any per action $+bug #019f268f-eb38-7614-b246-1d7d44c49322
    >[ ] delete act_matches and the mutations resolver, delegate to one implementation $ complete, update, cancel, and delete resolve through the same code path as plan.rs and the LSP; the ActionList-level entry can live in core beside reference.rs if the DomainModel shape is too heavy for file-local commands $+cli,library #019f268f-eb3a-7e79-b865-ac4c25dcba48
    >[ ] port the alias-before-name regression test to the surviving seam $ mutations.rs test_resolve_alias_before_name is the guard that documents the spec order — it must outlive the module it currently lives in $+testing #019f268f-eb3b-7adb-8fc6-1161be233e32
[ ] move subtree-close semantics into core $ what complete means — close the descendants, stamp completed_at, detach parents, move to the completed file — is business logic implemented inline in the CLI while core claims to own it. complete_action and cancel_action are fifty-line twins differing only in the target state $!2+library #019f268f-eb3c-7e0d-bcdd-f4bdb5c7bbc5
    >[ ] add close_subtree to core with tests $ one function taking the action list, root id, closing state, and timestamp; returns the closed subtree for the caller to append to the completed file. collect_subtree_ids moves with it. SEQUENCED after the action-lifecycle Action struct extension — cancelled_at and sidecar lifecycle ownership change what close_subtree must stamp; designing it first means immediate rework $+library  <07be46c7-e0c5-49eb-a67f-1a18002cb74b#019f268f-eb3d-7a1e-b19f-eb4810187d96
    >[ ] collapse complete_action and cancel_action onto it $ both become thin callers passing Completed or Cancelled; dry-run and messaging stay in the command layer $+cli #019f268f-eb3e-7ece-a4c4-1860b060f94a
[ ] deduplicate workspace config between CLI and core $ environment_reader::Config carries get_tag_ancestors, expand_tag, and expand_tags as character-for-character copies of WorkspaceConfig in core config.rs, including roughly ninety lines of duplicated tests — and core's copy is strictly better because it also has descendants_and_self $!2+cli #019f268f-eb3f-7238-928f-7fcb123ba985
    >[ ] delegate tag-hierarchy methods to WorkspaceConfig and delete the copied tests $ Config keeps loading, precedence, and cli_ fields; semantic methods live only in core. CommandContext already builds a WorkspaceConfig, so callers converge on that $+cli #019f268f-eb41-7389-aff1-6e7ff6cd43f0
[ ] sweep dead code and single-consumer compat shims $ nothing links these crates except the CLI binary itself — the nvim plugin shells out — so backward-compat layers are pure carrying cost $!2+cli #019f268f-eb43-7994-8d0f-13c024980696
    >[ ] delete the unused lib.rs surface $ merge_hashmaps has zero call sites; find_plan_file and find_plan_file_for_mutation are kept alive by allow dead_code; run_workspace_sql_query and load_workspace_actions have no callers — and the sql name is wrong anyway, it is SPARQL $+cli #019f268f-eb44-7fcc-8d3d-bffd32ce2539
    >[ ] make update_action use ActionUpdate and apply_updates or delete them $ the struct-based update pattern in mutations.rs is good design lying dead while update_action pokes ten positional params and reimplements it inline — same call as PlanFields already proves in the argparser $+cli #019f268f-eb45-749b-8142-8e1440b45eb8
    >[ ] drop the vestigial opts parameter from the parse wrapper chain $ get_action_list_struct threads an unused serde_json Value through tests and archive.rs — a leftover from the js-style options era $+cli #019f268f-eb47-7f57-b8c7-2ba766b74e7a
    >[ ] extract build_workspace_store from the query helpers $ run_workspace_raw_query and its siblings duplicate the create-store, insert-metadata, load-additional-workspaces dance; one helper returning the populated store collapses them to a few lines each $+cli #019f268f-eb48-7c81-ad4c-748ece362373
    >[ ] delete the redundant per-action ActionSource $ SourcedAction.source stamps a per-file value onto every action: load.rs:172 sets file_path to the same PathBuf MarkdownCharter.acts_file already holds (line 183), and .project is never read anywhere. the only two readers (graph/insert.rs:120, graph/jsonld.rs:51) already iterate charters, so they read the path from the enclosing group. 3 of 5 construction sites already pass dummy PathBuf::new(). delete ActionSource and the now-dead ActionRepository, drop the field, derive provenance from the file/charter group — the more proper structure surfaced by the doctor-inventory design 2026-07-03 $+library,cli #019f2a95-9447-7069-9604-e39ef1535549
[ ] adopt structured errors at the CLI boundary $ one hundred twenty-five Result String sites re-stringify errors core already types with thiserror, burying every call in map_err format noise. anyhow with context at the binary layer deletes most of it and improves the error output — the largest same-behavior-less-code win in the review $!3+cli #019f268f-eb49-7e1b-9e4b-6f93ebf25fda
    >[ ] convert the command layer to anyhow Result with context $ mechanical sweep, best done file-by-file after the seam work above so it does not conflict with everything $+cli #019f268f-eb4b-7b05-93be-92418918c451
[ ] record the call-site sweep done-gate in the process spec $ the durable lesson — a core capability is not done until CLI call sites are swept onto it and a guard exists — belongs in specifications process.md so future charters inherit it instead of rediscovering it $!3+documentation #019f268f-eb4c-7384-b316-a3b880291ab4
